post_text:
Character trait: Citizenship
Being a good citizen means doing your share to make your school and community a better place, either by yourself or through cooperation with others. A good citizen stays informed and gets involved in local affairs, always striving to make the community a better place. A good citizen is a good neighbor who obeys the law, protects the environment and volunteers to help others.

When discussing this pillar with your student, tell them how they can be a good citizen by volunteering, helping others and being a contributing member of society.

post_text: We continued to work on our Earth Day gardening project today! We made ollas (pronounced oh-yahs), which are clay pots filled with water. The porous walls of the olla allow for water to dissipate into the soil as needed. Because the pores in the clay pot are small, the water does not freely flow out of the pot. This is an ancient watering technique developed more than 4,000 years ago. It is a great way to help the plants develop strong root systems and have a better chance to survive our arid climate!

post_text:
Monday, Oct. 28 is our "Mix It Up at Lunch Day" at La Paloma Lakeside.

Mix It Up at Lunch is a simple call to action for students of all grades: Sit next to someone new in the cafeteria. Whether they choose their own seats or sit where they’re assigned, most students eat lunch in a bubble, surrounded by the same people. Those habits lead to division. When school leaders encourage students to try something new, even if just for a day, they are helping them to bridge differences and build an important skill.

Learn more:
https://www.tolerance.org/mix-it-up

In an effort to promote character awareness, La Paloma Lakeside will be offering free character dress down days every Wednesday! If students wish to participate, they are to wear the color of the month for that character trait. Let’s show everyone how we show CHARACTER!

August - Trustworthy Blue
September and October - Respectful Yellow
November and December - Responsible Green
January - Fairness Orange
February and March - Caring Red
April and May - Citizenship Purple
